<TITLE> Security agencies speed up anticrime efforts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 24 (bdnews24.com)  Law-enforcement agencies stepped up their operations across the country Monday in the wake of a spike in crimes. "Ongoing crime control operations have been strengthened countrywide following a law and order meeting held Monday," RAB director general Hassan Mahmood Khandkar told bdnews24.com Tuesday. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed had a meeting with heads of the law-enforcement agencies Monday The meeting drew up a list of "must dos" to arrest the deterioration in the law and order situation. Fakhruddin said the law enforcers would be held accountable for any future breaches in public security. The activities of the intelligence gathering services have also been heightened with fresh operations being planned on their findings, the RAB chief said. "Crime control operations were stepped up after the murder of a woman lawyer recently. That is how the suspected killer was apprehended so quickly," Khandkar said. Huge numbers of plainclothesmen have been deployed in crowded places such as bus terminals, railway stations and ferry piers. In addition, the public were being routinely screened on the outskirts of cities, where some will be frisked and their luggage searched. bdnews24.com/lh/
